back delivery
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a tilter or harvesting machine [used since the 1860s] which `delivers' its grain at the rear rather than at the side.


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
